reviewText:
Intelligent, various and humorous puzzle-platformer with poor developer's support.

It's about:wimp chasing theft to get back his sacred treasure - pants;
jumping and walking through level avoiding traps and/or overcome obstacles;
solving different kind of puzzles: the core of each puzzle is getting a paper roll for higher score or pants to obtain access to the next level, more pants - more joy, more rolls - more relieve;
indirect fights with boss(es).
Why you should play this:you like puzzles and platformers, but don't want to jump too much (or train your reaction) and don't look for brain-melting riddles;
gameplay's multeity:
development approach - progressing through levels wimp obtains abilities to morph to another condition (Fire, Frost, Portal), each one offers special perk helping to solve the puzzle and complete the level;
vivid level's enviroment: moving platfroms, controls, cardboxes, fans, portals - everything takes part in shaping the puzzle, everything is a test area for wimp's abilities;
simple physics" presented as well: wimp can stick do the platforms to get somewhere or use swing inertness

Pros:
- Combination of platformer and puzzle gameplay;
- 4 different gameplay mechanics on 4 different worlds (sticky, fire, teleportation and ice);
- absolutely beautiful and good looking graphics even on huge TV screen;
- smooth controls;
- friendly for children and girls;

Cons:
- first world less interesting than other three worlds.

So I definitely recommend it. Especially for its low price.
